american teacher screening and town hall meeting education and society theme house american teacher screening and town hall meeting submitted by daniel wong on thu 01 26 2012 00 30 join east house for american teacher american teacher tells the collective story of our nation's 3.2 million teachers capturing the day to day lives and sacrifices of public school teachers through footage of four individuals who spend every day in the classroom the film brings to light how little we value our most effective teachers and the effect this has on the education of our students we are excited to host an interactive panel discussion with former teachers and education experts discussion will be moderated by christine min wotipka stanford school of education professor panelists include salina gray former teacher and current stanford phd student ira lit stanford school of education professor susan o hara stanford school of education professor alexis patterson former teacher and current stanford phd student rsvp now the event is free and open to the stanford community but an rsvp is necessary for entry this event is made possible by the generous support of the charles f riddell fund and residential education login to post comments home welcome we are the education and society theme east house directions here we seek to establish the salience of education and the relationship between education and society on stanford campus through outreach to undergraduates and residential based programming please contact us with any comments or suggestions new forum topics photographs for waiting for superman more user login username password request new password education and society theme house calendar of events programs at east living at east bulletin board about us contact us visit the education theme house at 544 governor's avenue between lagunita and frosoco drupal theme designed by blamcast
